  <prompt>
    Build the natural-language regression test suite per spec FR-54 + NFR-11: confirm
    natural-language requests still work alongside slashes. The CommandRouter parser MUST
    return `command: null` for non-slash input, and the existing `CapabilityRouter` Layer 1/2/3
    classification path MUST remain unchanged.

    This is the binding regression gate for Pillar 8's backward-compat promise. R5
    `CapabilityRouter` behavior is production-mature; R6 Pillar 8 adds the CommandRouter layer
    in front but MUST NOT break existing natural-language routing.

    Test surface:
    - "summarize this document" (natural-language equivalent of `/summarize`) → routes via
      CapabilityRouter to SUM-CHAT playbook; no `commandIntent` metadata set.
    - "draft a reply to the opposing counsel" (natural-language equivalent of `/draft`) →
      routes via CapabilityRouter to draft tools.
    - "what's the matter status?" (general conversational query) → no playbook; agent
      responds conversationally (NFR-01).
    - "make it shorter" (refinement, no slashes, follows up on prior summary) → agent stays
      conversational.

    Tests assert: (a) `Intent.command === null` for each natural-language input; (b) chat-endpoint
    payload has `commandIntent: null` (or omitted); (c) CapabilityRouter logs Layer 1/2 classification
    matches expected pre-Pillar-8 behavior (use existing telemetry); (d) conversational follow-ups
    work (NFR-01).

    Frontend-only task; BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend integration-test engineer with familiarity with CapabilityRouter 3-tier classification
    and the SpaarkeAi conversation pane. Comfortable with regression-test design that asserts
    "behavior X must continue to work despite change Y".
  </role>

  <goal>
    Regression test file exists; covers 4+ natural-language inputs; asserts CommandRouter parser
    returns `command: null` and CapabilityRouter path unchanged. NFR-11 + NFR-01 verifiable
    via test suite.
  </goal>

